-- Cyprus Church to Participate in Natural Gas Drilling, CyBC Says
-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 2012-09-07T12:33:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-07/cyprus-church-to-participate-in-natural-gas-drilling-cybc-says.html
The Orthodox Christian Church of
Cyprus will work with an international company that has made an
application to drill for natural gas in the country’s exclusive
economic zone,  CyBC  said, citing Archbishop Chrysostomos II.  The church plans to use property as collateral in order to
acquire a share in natural gas drilling and distribution
activities, the Nicosia-based state-broadcaster today, citing
the church leader as saying in a TV interview in its ‘From Day
to Day’ program.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Tugwell in Athens at 
 ptugwell1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jerrold Colten at 
